THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 226 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. 1. The State Treasurer shall establish by regulation
4 a program to provide:
5 (a) Reimbursement for tuition charges, registration fees,
6 laboratory fees, examination fees, licensure fees or certification
7 fees and any other fees paid to an institution within the Nevada
8 System of Higher Education or to a professional or occupational
9 licensing board or regulatory body of this State by a person who is
10 in financial need and preparing for employment in professions in
11 K-12 education or health care.
12 (b) Grants to hospitals to create, expand or fund programs in
13 which a hospital coordinates with a secondary school to provide
14 work-based learning opportunities for students.
15 2. The program must include a process for a person to apply
16 for reimbursement or a grant described in subsection 1.
17 3. The State Treasurer shall consult with the State Board of
18 Education before approving any application for a grant.
19 4. The regulations adopted pursuant to this section must
20 prescribe, without limitation:
21 (a) The criteria for eligibility to receive money from the
22 program; and
23 (b) Procedures for the submission and review of applications
24 to receive money from the program.
25 Sec. 3. 1. The Nevada Education and Health Care
26 Pathways Account is hereby created in the State General Fund.
27 The Account must be administered by the State Treasurer.
28 2. The money in the Account must be used to carry out the
29 program established pursuant to section 2 of this act.
30 3. The State Treasurer may apply for and accept any
31 donation, gift, grant, bequest or other source of money for deposit
32 in the Account.
33 4. The interest and income earned on money in the Account,
34 after deducting any applicable charges, must be credited to the
35 Account.
36 5. Any money in the Account remaining at the end of a fiscal
37 year does not revert to the State General Fund, and the balance in
38 the Account must be carried forward to the next fiscal year.
